### Elixir

1. Elixir is a functional, immutable language built on the Erlang VM (BEAM), designed for highly concurrent,
	fault tolerant systems.

2. 	Ruby vs Elixir (MOST IMPORTANT QUESTION)
	How to answer (memorize this)
	
	Ruby				Elixir
	Object-oriented		Functional
	Mutable objects		Immutable data
	Threads / GIL		Lightweight processes (BEAM)
	Exceptions			â€œLet it crashâ€
	Shared memory		Message passing

3.	Key line to say:

	â€œElixir achieves concurrency using lightweight processes and message passing instead of shared mutable state.â€

