	map: %{name: "Shubham", age: 30}

	access: user.name


6. Concurrency (THIS IS WHY ELIXIR EXISTS)
	Core idea
	Thousands of lightweight processes

	Each process has its own memory

	Communicate via messages

	Example:
		spawn(fn ->
		  IO.puts("Hello from process")
		end)


		Say this confidently:

		â€œElixir processes are not OS threads. They are lightweight and managed by the BEAM VM.â€

7.		GenServer (High chance question)
		What is GenServer?

		A behavior for implementing server-like processes with state.

		Simple explanation

		Handles state

		Handles messages

		Runs in its own process

		Interview answer:

		â€œGenServer is used to manage stateful processes in a concurrent and fault-tolerant way.â€

		No need to code unless asked.

